page.title: 09MY TYPICAL DAY II
page.content:

Dinner time lasts until one o'clock. The dinner ladies let us in. We have one lesson when we come inside and after that we have playtime. We go back inside at half past two and have one more lesson before it is time for everyone to go home at three thirty. In the evenings I spend most of my time watching television until five o'clock and then I have my tea. At half past five I do my piano practice. When I have done that I either go out to play or stay in and watch television.
